'''The Benny Award''' is the highest honour that can be bestowed to a New Zealand [[Variety Show|variety]] entertainer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/taranaki-daily-news/entertainment/8525612/Friends-on-tour-with-country-music-lineup|title=Friends on tour with country music lineup, Taranaki Daily News Online}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amplifier.co.nz/news/64076/benny-award-goes-to-gary-daverne-onzm.html|title=Amplifer News Story : Gary Daverne Benny Award|access-date=2013-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120419062309/http://www.amplifier.co.nz/news/64076/benny-award-goes-to-gary-daverne-onzm.html|archive-date=2012-04-19|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref><ref name="voxy">{{cite web|url=http://www.voxy.co.nz/national/eddie-low-honoured-benny-award/5/28061|title=Voxy News - Eddie Low Honoured with Benny Award}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.livecabaretshows.com/jimjoll.htm|title=Jim Joll Biography}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.azshows.com/TheaterTickets/review/audience/symphony-orchestra-conductors-third-year-to-see-shen-yun/|title=Shen Yun Performing Arts Website, Gary Daverne}}</ref><ref name="vac_a">{{cite web|url=http://www.vac.org.nz/|title=VAC Website}}</ref>  It is presented annually by the [[Variety Artists Club of New Zealand]], a non-for-profit organisation and showbusiness club, founded in 1966 and awarded to a variety performer who has achieved "A lifetime of excellence in their field of the performing arts".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.stuff.co.nz/entertainment/682232/Kiwi-pop-singer-receives-Benny-Award|title=Suzanne Lynch Benny Award Article, Stuff.co.nz}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amplifier.co.nz/news/52510/eddie-low-honoured-with-benny-award.html|title=Eddie Low Benny Award, NZ Music News|access-date=2013-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402112120/http://www.amplifier.co.nz/news/52510/eddie-low-honoured-with-benny-award.html|archive-date=2015-04-02|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref>

==Nominations==

Nominations for the Benny Award are accepted from VAC members and the recipient ultimately decided upon by past Benny recipients, making its presentation recognition of the highest degree by the New Zealand entertainment industry.<ref name="voxy" /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.raycolumbus.com/past.html|title=Ray Columbus Biography}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nzonscreen.com/person/chic-littlewood/biography|title=Chic Littlewood Biography - NZOnScreen}}</ref>

==Naming==

The Benny Award was named after its first recipient, legendary New Zealand variety performer [[Edgar Wilson Benyon|Edgar Benyon]] (1902-1978) in 1969.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.teara.govt.nz/en/biographies/5b25/1|title=Edgar Benyon Biography, Encyclopedia of NZ Biography}}</ref>  The Benny statuette was designed and sculptured by magician Jon Zealando and features Greek muses [[Melpomene]] and [[Thalia (muse)|Thalia]] - the traditional symbols of comedy and tragedy.<ref name="vac">{{cite web|url=http://www.vacnz.com/bennyaward|title=Benny Awards Page, VAC Website}}</ref>

Recipients of the Benny Award include many New Zealand household names and figureheads of entertainment.<ref name="voxy" /><ref name="aucklandcity.govt.nz">{{cite web|url=
http://www.aucklandcity.govt.nz/dbtw-wpd/exec/dbtwpub.dll?AC=SEE_ALSO&QF0=Descriptors&QI0==%22Benny+Award%22&XC=/dbtw-wpd/exec/dbtwpub.dll&BU=&TN=LocHAM&SN=AUTO10888&SE=52&RN=4&MR=0&TR=0&TX=1000&ES=0&CS=1&XP=&RF=Displayweb&EF=&DF=&RL=0&EL=0&DL=0&NP=2&ID=&MF=WPEngMsg.ini&MQ=&TI=0&DT=&ST=0&IR=49036&NR=0&NB=0&SV=0&SS=0&BG=&FG=&QS=&OEX=ISO-8859-1&OEH=ISO-8859-1|title=Auckland City Library Records - Benny Award}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nzmusic.org.nz/artists/pop/ray-columbus/|title=New Zealand Music Commission, Columbus Biography}}</ref>

